<DOC><DOCNO> AP900216-0192 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-16-90 2118EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Switzerland-Train     02-16 0231</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Switzerland-Train,0238</SECOND><HEAD>Three Killed, 12 Injured in Swiss Train Crash</HEAD><DATELINE>SAXON, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Three people were killed and 12injured early Friday when an overnight express train traveling fromMilan to Paris smashed into the rear of a railway maintenancetrain, authorities said.   Killed were the train engineers, both Swiss, and a 19-year-oldSwiss passenger, son of the passenger train's conductor, FederalRailways chief Claude Roux told reporters.   Roux said the ``Galilei'' express had a green light and wastraveling at 75 mph when it hit the maintenance train from behindin this southwestern Swiss town. The express train, comprised of anengine and six sleeping cars, derailed.   Most of the 420 passengers were asleep when the crash occurredat 1:45 a.m., Roux said. They were mostly French, Italian andBritish.   Two 16-year-old Italian girls were seriously injured. Alsoreported injured were six other Italian passengers, three Frenchand a Turkish railway worker.   Roux said human error was suspected in the crash because themaintenance train was not moved off the main track in time. Theengine and two cars were being used to service overhead electricalwires.   It was the worst rail wreck in Switzerland since five peoplewere killed in the head-on crash of a local train with an enginenear Lausanne in 1985.   Train traffic through lower Valais canton was expected to beinterrupted until Saturday.</TEXT></DOC>